Package: statistics
Version: 0.12
Title: Miscellanea Functions For Intro Stats Classes
Authors@R: person(
  given = "Adrian", family = "Dusa",
  role = c("aut", "cre", "cph"),
  email = "dusa.adrian@unibuc.ro",
  comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0002-3525-9253"))
Depends: R (>= 3.5.0)
License: GPL (>= 3)
Imports: admisc (>= 0.25), declared (> 0.15)
Description: Utilities for introductory statistics labs: plot tail or interval
  areas for the normal or t distributions, highlight binomial probabilities, and
  summarise discrete random variables. Calculate pooled standard deviations and
  Welch-Satterthwaite degrees of freedom, and run teaching-friendly tests such as
  Fligner-Killeen plus one-way ANOVA, and t tests with an Ansari-Bradley variance
  check alongside pooled and Welch variants.
